        "title": {
          "english": "Asking about masculine objects: What is this?"
        },
        "text": "To ask \"What is this?\" when referring to a masculine object in Levantine Arabic, we use \"شو هادا؟\". This phrase is commonly used in everyday conversation.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "شو هادا؟",
            "english": "What is this? (masculine)",
            "transliteration": "Shu hada?"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Vocabulary: Book"
        },
        "text": "The word for \"book\" in Levantine Arabic is \"كتاب\". It is a masculine noun. Pay attention to its pronunciation.",
