        "title": {
          "english": "Adjective: Big"
        },
        "text": "The adjective for \"big\" is \"كبير\" for masculine nouns and \"كبيرة\" for feminine nouns. Adjectives in Arabic typically follow the noun they describe and must agree in gender.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "كتاب كبير",
            "english": "A big book (masculine)",
            "transliteration": "kitāb kabīr"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "طاولة كبيرة",
            "english": "A big table (feminine)",
            "transliteration": "ṭāwleh kabīreh"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Adjective: Small"
        },
        "text": "The adjective for \"small\" is \"صغير\" for masculine nouns and \"صغيرة\" for feminine nouns. Remember to match the gender of the adjective to the noun.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "قلم صغير",
            "english": "A small pen (masculine)",
            "transliteration": "qalam ṣaghīr"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "شنطة صغيرة",
            "english": "A small bag (feminine)",
            "transliteration": "shanṭa ṣaghīreh"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Asking about size"
        },
        "text": "To ask \"Is it big or small?\" you combine the adjectives with \"أو\" (aw) meaning \"or\". You adjust the adjectives for gender: \"كبير أو صغير؟\" for masculine and \"كبيرة أو صغيرة؟\" for feminine objects.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "هادا كتاب، كبير أو صغير؟",
            "english": "This is a book, big or small?",
            "transliteration": "Hada kitāb, kabīr aw ṣaghīr?"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "هادي طاولة، كبيرة أو صغيرة؟",
            "english": "This is a table, big or small?",
            "transliteration": "Hadi ṭāwleh, kabīreh aw ṣaghīreh?"
          }
        ]
      }
